The "Year the Sun Died" is the third studio album by American heavy & power  metal band Sanctuary, released through Century Media Records. It is Sanctuary's first studio album since 1989's "Into the Mirror Black", and their first release with former Forced Entry guitarist Brad Hull, making it the band's first studio album without Sean Blosl.
